text: Union Mill (also known as Union Mills) is an unincorporated community in Thurston County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== Union Mill had its start in 1901. The community took its name from Union Mills, a local sawmill. A post office called Union Mill was established in 1911, and remained in operation until 1931. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Thurston County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Union Mill, Washington
